context: <b7_0>Houston was founded<b7_0/> in <a0_0>1836<a0_0/> on land near the banks of <a1_0><b5_0><b6_0>Buffalo Bayou<b6_0/><b5_0/><a1_0/> (now known as Allen's Landing) and incorporated as a city on <a2_0><b8_0>June 5, 1837<b8_0/><a2_0/>. The city was named after former General <a3_0>Sam Houston<a3_0/>, who was president of the Republic of Texas and had commanded and won at the <a4_0>Battle of San Jacinto<a4_0/> 25 miles (40 km) east of where the city was established.
